**Step 2: Observations and Strategy**

* **Symmetry:** Observe the symmetry in the diagram. Lines
  I<sub>B</sub>I<sub>C</sub> and E<sub>B</sub>E<sub>C</sub> are parallel since they are formed by external bisectors. This symmetry will be helpful.

* **Area Breakdown:**  The quadrilateral I<sub>B</sub>I<sub>C</sub>E<sub>B</sub>E<sub>C</sub> can be divided into triangle I<sub>B</sub>I<sub>C</sub>D and two triangles/trapezoids.  

We know the areas of triangles I<sub>B</sub>I<sub>C</sub>D and I<sub>B</sub>I<sub>C</sub>E<sub>B</sub>E<sub>C</sub>, and we need to find the area of triangle ABC.
